Author: johannah12345
Content:
Y**our Input Needed: Help Us Understand Inclusivity in Esports for People with Disabilities **                                                                                                    I hope this message finds you well. As a member of the esports research network and the esports community (no matter whether player, researcher, lecturer, coach, manager, spectator, etc.), your insights and experiences are incredibly valuable to us. We as a research team from the University of Siegen/Germany (www.pmg.uni-siegen.de) are conducting an empirical study to explore the reasons behind the inclusivity of people with disabilities in esports. Your participation in this research will provide crucial data to better understand the current state and the motivations for inclusivity within this rapidly growing field.
 
We have designed a brief online questionnaire that aims to assess how and why people with disabilities are included in esports and where a transfer to human resource management education could make sense.
 
The survey will take no more than 5 minutes of your time, and your responses will be anonymous and used solely for research purposes.
 
You can access the questionnaire via the following link : https://qr.de/6yTZru
 
We would be extremely grateful if you could take a few minutes to complete the questionnaire. Additionally, we would appreciate it if you could share the  link within your local esports community to help us gather a wide range of perspectives.
 
Thank you in advance for your participation and support. Your contribution is invaluable to our research and will help us to promote a more inclusive esports environment for everyone.
 
Best regards,
Volker & Johanna

______________________________________
Univ.-Prof. Dr. Volker Stein
Universit√§t Siegen
Lehrstuhl f√ºr Betriebswirtschaftslehre, insb.

Content:
Hey, It looks like you manually enabled certain regions, there's a chance UK wasn't included in your toggles. As the page would say Global (Shown below).

Head over to Organizer actions while you are on the [tournament page](https://www.communitygaming.io/tournament/wombat-one-tap-tournament), and then click Edit Tournament.

Once you're there, scroll down to the regions, and click "global".

If you need any other assistance, head over to #choose-a-region so you can choose a region of your choice, and then open up a Helpdesk ticket so one of our support agents or community managers can assist ;D

Author: zleets
Content:
I swear, this is so ridiculous! How can my account be flagged as suspicious when I haven't done anything wrong? This is a gaming community, for crying out loud! Since when do people have to verify their identity just to play games? It's insane! I'm genuinely scared to go through with this verification because my data could easily be misused. This is just a gaming community, for playing games, and now you want us to verify our faces? Why should we have to deal with face verification? Games are supposed to be fun, not a headache!

Honestly, I feel concerned about the policy that asks for personal data, even though it is claimed that it will not be shared with third parties. In fact, there are alternatives like Gitcoin Passport that can be used for verification without the need for KYC on a platform I've never tried before. I'm deeply disappointed by this situation. There should be a safer and more transparent solution. Many people are affected, not just me, and I sympathize with those who haven't spoken up yet.

Author: crown6189
Content: Sorry you had to experience that , create a ticket and tag the team

Author: valdizney
Content:
Hey @Zleets thanks for raising your concerns, I tottaly understand where you're coming from. The verification process is aimed at protecting the community from bad actors, but I get why it feels like a huge leap, especially when we‚Äôre just here to game. Your concerns about privacy and data security are completely valid, and it‚Äôs great that you brought up alternatives like Gitcoin Passport.

Let me assure you that we take privacy seriously and the data won‚Äôt be shared with third parties. I‚Äôll pass along your feedback to the team so we can explore more transparent and flexible solutions moving forward. You‚Äôre not alone in this, and we want to make sure everyone can game in a safe, enjoyable environment. Stay tuned, we‚Äôll keep you updated!

Author: chillandrew1511
Content: yep, I'm just a user too. And I'm also reading everyone's discussion about it. I'm pretty neutral on the identity verification process in the internet space, but I have to admit that the service the project is providing here is popular and familiar. But aside from the GP verification proposal, it still requires KYC if you want to have a high score and that's a difficult process for most especially newbies. Simplifying the problem here, some cases are labeled as fraud, but I think any service has its own rules. The blockchain/crypto space needs a combination of decentralized and centralized so be comfortable with the binding process. Anyway, I think we all here want the best from this project, and this is just a small part of the operating procedures, I still like to look at the fact that the feature of this product is really potential in the gamefi environment, hopefully we will see the next useful information soon.

Author: zleets
Content: I apologize for any confusion I caused earlier. It stemmed from my lack of knowledge about the matter. However, I still stand by my opinion that games shouldn't require KYC. In my experience playing cryptocurrency-based games, none have implemented KYC. While there might be some exceptions, none of the major projects, such as Sandbox or Pixel, use KYC. Therefore, I don't agree with its use in gaming, especially in crypto games, where it's uncommon.

Author: chillandrew1511
Content: In addition, I also have some opinions about social platforms with community like x, meta, tele... kyc is only suitable for some specific files. But here, reviewing the issue, it is not mandatory here for this project, just some exceptions (maybe violating the rules), anyway, I think everything with the project is still operating on a good trajectory.
